## 1. Railway Maintenance Domain

### 1.1 ECM Framework (EU 2019/779)

The **Entity in Charge of Maintenance (ECM)** framework establishes legal responsibilities for railway vehicle maintenance across European railway networks. While Dubai Metro is outside EU jurisdiction, the ECM framework represents industry best practice and provides a compliance-ready architecture.

#### 1.1.1 ECM Function Mapping

| Function | Responsibility | MMS V1.0 Feature | V1.0 Status |
|----------|----------------|------------------|-------------|
| **ECM-F1** | Maintenance Management | Dashboard KPIs, compliance tracking | Visualization only |
| **ECM-F2** | Maintenance Development | Interval definitions, plan visualization | Mock data display |
| **ECM-F3** | Fleet Maintenance Management | Real-time fleet status, conflict detection | Conflict indicators |
| **ECM-F4** | Maintenance Delivery | Work order visualization, depot allocation | Visual representation |

#### 1.1.2 ECM Compliance Requirements

| Requirement | ECM Article | MMS V1.0 Implementation | V1.1+ Roadmap |
|-------------|-------------|------------------------|---------------|
| Risk assessment | Art. 5.2 | Conflict detection, overdue warnings | Automated alerts |
| Competence management | Art. 5.3 | Not implemented | Resource skill tracking |
| Documentation | Art. 5.4 | Not implemented | Audit trail logging |
| Performance monitoring | Art. 5.5 | KPI display | Fleet availability metrics |

#### 1.1.3 ECM Traceability Requirements (Future)

Full ECM compliance requires traceability of all maintenance decisions:

- Immutable audit logs of all scheduling decisions
- Justification records for allocation recommendations
- Historical mileage tracking with timestamps
- Decision override justifications

**V1.0 Scope:** Visualization only. Audit trail deferred to V1.1.

