### 1.2 RAMS Compliance (EN 50126-1)

**RAMS** = Reliability, Availability, Maintainability, Safety

EN 50126-1:2017 defines the railway RAMS lifecycle and requirements. MMS visualizes RAMS metrics but does not implement automated RAMS analysis in V1.0.

#### 1.2.1 RAMS Metric Definitions

| Aspect | Standard | Definition | MMS V1.0 Feature |
|--------|----------|------------|------------------|
| **Reliability** | EN 50126-1 Section 6 | Probability that system performs intended function under stated conditions for specified period | MTBF display |
| **Availability** | EN 50126-1 Section 7 | Ability to be in a state to perform a required function at a given instant | Fleet availability % |
| **Maintainability** | EN 50126-1 Section 8 | Probability that maintenance can be performed within stated time | MTTR display |
| **Safety** | EN 50126-1 Section 9 | Freedom from unacceptable risk of harm | Critical task priority |

#### 1.2.2 RAMS Targets

| Metric | Formula | Target | Critical Threshold |
|--------|---------|--------|-------------------|
| Fleet Availability | (Fit Trains / Total Trains) x 100 | >= 97% | < 95% |
| MTBF | Total Operating Hours / Number of Failures | Operator-defined | Operator-defined |
| MTTR | Total Downtime Hours / Number of Repairs | <= 24 hours | > 48 hours |
| Schedule Adherence | (On-Time Maintenance / Scheduled Maintenance) x 100 | >= 95% | < 90% |

