### 4.5 Km Penalty Calculation (Solver)

Used by the allocation solver to prioritize under-utilized trains.

#### 4.5.1 Formula

```
deviation_pct = |current_km - target_km| / max(target_km, 1) * 100

If current_km < target_km:
  penalty = -deviation_pct * 10  (BONUS - negative = good)

If current_km >= target_km:
  penalty = +deviation_pct * 10  (PENALTY - positive = bad)
```

#### 4.5.2 TypeScript Implementation

```typescript
function calculateKmPenalty(
  currentKm: number,
  targetKm: number,
  fleetAvgKm: number
): number {
  const effectiveTarget = targetKm || fleetAvgKm;
  if (effectiveTarget === 0) return 0;

  const deviationPct = Math.abs(currentKm - effectiveTarget) / effectiveTarget * 100;

  if (currentKm < effectiveTarget) {
    return -Math.round(deviationPct * 10);  // Bonus for under-utilized
  } else {
    return Math.round(deviationPct * 10);   // Penalty for over-utilized
  }
}
```

